    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": ".",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 22.83
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Yeah long story.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 24.91
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Tell me a long story.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 35.98
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Once upon a time, nestled deep within a valley perpetually draped in mist, lay the village of Everglen.",
      "at_sec": 36.93
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "It was known throughout the land for its skilled clockmakers, artisans who crafted intricate timepieces that were not just beautiful but seemed to hum with a gentle magic.",
      "at_sec": 37.5
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Among them lived a young woman named Elara, whose talent surpassed even the most seasoned masters.",
      "at_sec": 37.84
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "But Elara held a secret sorrow.",
      "at_sec": 37.98
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "She longed to create a clock that could capture not just time, but memories - the fleeting moments of joy, sorrow, and everything in between.",
      "at_sec": 38.49
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The village elder, a wizened man named Silas, had often told Elara the legend of the \"Chronarium Bloom,\" a mythical flower said to bloom only once a century, its petals imbued with the essence of captured moments.",
      "at_sec": 39.34
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "He warned her, however, that seeking it was perilous, guarded by ancient spirits and treacherous landscapes.",
      "at_sec": 39.69
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Yet, Elara's desire burned too fiercely to be deterred.",
      "at_sec": 39.94
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "One misty morning, she left Everglen, armed with her tools, a map Silas had drawn, and a heart full of hope.",
      "at_sec": 40.46
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Her journey took her through whispering forests where trees seemed to lean in and share secrets, across shimmering rivers guarded by playful sprites, and over mountains that scraped the sky.",
      "at_sec": 41.06
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "She faced trials \u2013 outsmarting mischievous goblins who tried to steal her tools, soothing a grieving willow spirit who blocked her path, and navigating a labyrinth of illusions created by a lonely faerie queen.",
      "at_sec": 41.79
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Finally, after many weeks, she reached the Valley of Echoes, where the Chronarium Bloom was said to grow.",
      "at_sec": 42.25
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The air here thrummed with a strange energy, and ghostly whispers carried on the wind.",
      "at_sec": 42.59
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "In the center of the valley, bathed in a soft, ethereal light, stood a single, luminous flower\u2014the Chronarium Bloom.",
      "at_sec": 43.1
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "But it was guarded by a formidable spirit, a being of swirling mist and starlight, who identified itself as the Keeper of Memories.",
      "at_sec": 43.6
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "\u201cYou seek the Bloom\u2019s essence,\u201d the Keeper said, its voice like the chime of distant bells.",
      "at_sec": 44.01
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "\u201cBut memories are fragile, and their power can be dangerous.",
      "at_sec": 44.26
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Why do you desire to capture them?\u201d",
      "at_sec": 44.4
    }
  ],
